{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"46c78bfb-12c9-4988-8169-b2924693a14d","content":"Neither — use **`dotnet watch`** to benefit from hot reload.\n\n- **`dotnet watch test`** – re-runs tests automatically when you save a file.\n- **`dotnet watch run`** – for apps (not applicable to a test project).\n\nSince your project is a test project, run:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test\n```\n\n`dotnet test` and `dotnet run` are one-shot commands — they don't monitor for file changes. The `watch` command is what triggers hot reload / re-execution on save.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"26af6465-c667-4316-bd61-6e3042805dc9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to use hot reload with .NET testing. Let me look at the project files to understand the context better.","outputTokens":170,"requestId":"A808:34550C:60D6F7B:695FF42:6A034B79"},"id":"7eb187b5-6842-44f1-8f3e-e51ff05e83e4","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:47:12.833Z","parentId":"0278d737-e8a2-47c9-81eb-f1820994f992"}
